        "hgios_score": 6,
        "tags": [],
        "what_text": "Attainment in literacy and numeracy has been exceptionally strong over time. Pupils at Bearsden Academy consistently perform above the Virtual Comparator, National and Local Authority benchmarks.\n\nThe school was awarded the “Reading Schools” Gold award for its commitment to supporting literacy and reading in the school community through reading time for young people, a strong culture of sharing reading and links to primary school reading initiatives.\n\nThere is whole school work to support the development of literacy and numeracy, through whole school moderation events, departmental moderation and collegiate processes for evidence sharing across the school.\n\nLeavers data shows, over the last four years, almost all learners achieve level 5 in both literacy and numeracy, and the rate of leavers achieving level 6 literacy and numeracy is well above the Virtual Comparator. \n\nIn most of the last 5 years, 100% of EAL and FSM and Q1 SIMD learners have achieved level 5 literacy. ASN pupils are ahead of virtual comparators.\n\nThe school has intervention approaches for all young people to gain a literacy or numeracy award where they are able to engage with the school. Most learners naturally achieve this award via a full course award – pass rates and presentation rates for English and Mathematics are regularly the highest in the local authority.",
