        "what_text": "The Pupil Improvement Team was established in the school in 2024 and builds on previous pupil voice initiatives (Bearsden Aspirational Team). Over fifty young people from S1-S6 volunteered to take part in this leadership opportunity.  The annual cycle highlights the opportunities young people have throughout the year to be actively involved in decision making processes.  Young people elect to be part of an ‘Improvement Team’ group and work alongside a staff link. \n\nYoung people engage with ‘How Good is OUR School?’ Statements and discuss strengths and next steps for L & T with their peers. They present their findings at year group assemblies, and all young people can provide further feedback through a Form on Satchel One/by joining the team. Young people meet with staff links to create action plans which are then shared at a Business Breakfast with parents/carers and other school community partners. The self-evaluative work from The Pupil Improvement team informs school improvement priorities. ‘You said, we did’ assemblies take place at the end of the school year. \n\nThe action plans for the Pupil Improvement Team were shared with Principal Teachers to support learning and teaching dialogue within the departments. The Pupil Improvement Team’s first assemblies have also been shared with all staff and support staff in the school. The feedback from the Pupil Improvement Team is used to support school improvement priorities.  \n\nRepresentatives from the Pupil Improvement Team will also present at a Parent Leadership twilight to highlight their work.\n\n\n\n",
