        "what_text": "Bearsden Academy has seen a steady improvement in attainment over time. To support this improvement, the school undergoes cycles of improvement, based around the framework provided by East Dunbartonshire Council.\n\nEach year, three-year priorities are agreed and planned out for the session. In order to shape the priorities, the school takes input from:\n\n- Existing feedback from previous priorities – this includes data gathered through strategic roles, pupil improvement team feedback, parent feedback from events, and feedback from the parent council\n\n- Staff, parent and pupil discussion on next steps and priorities – this has taken various forms depending on availability and timing. Improvement teams may review their work and indicate action points, for both staff and pupils. Parent leaders have informed our planning through meeting feedback, or feedback sessions. \n\n- Local Authority priorities are matched in to the plan and the plan is reviewed by senior leaders and the Parent Council\n\n- Plans are sent to professional associations for feedback, and to the local authority.\n\n## Supporting the Improvement Cycle\n\n- Almost all staff are engaged with the improvement team process, with the majority names in actions\n\n- Pupil groups consult with all pupils and frame feedback against key priorities for the school, such as meta-skills development and learning and teaching.\n\n- Ongoing discussion of these priorities through tripartite and extended meetings helps shape for the future – including Business Breakfasts, parent discussions and pupil leadership groups.\n\nThe process each year is reviewed through a Standards and Quality report, a Self Evaluation Report, and a Scoping Report, all submitted to the local authority for feedback.\n\nThe school also maintains its own evidence base, scoping framework and self evaluation scoring spreadsheet.\n\n## Departmental level improvement\n\nDepartments submit their own improvement cycle documents focused on their own actions, and the overlapping school actions. This includes:\n\n- Improvement plans for all departments\n\n- Standards and quality responses that highlight departmental contributions to the school\n\n- Interim and Final evaluation against the four main HGIOS Quality Indicators\n\n## Pupil Improvement\n\n- Pupils form groups around the priorities they wish to work with, and create action plans to share with Improvement team staff leads\n\n- This continues the development of our priorities and demonstrates an aligned approach to improvement\n\n- Pupil improvement updates are shared will all pupils\n\n",
