        "what_text": "Over the last two sessions, we have been looking to embed values-based communication into everything we do. This includes communicating with pupils via Registration and Assembly.\n\nOur school values were created through consultation with parents, staff and pupils. In 2023, surveys and discussions allowed us to narrow down values to five: respect, compassion, inclusion, equity and integrity.\n\nPupils in the Senior Phase then designed their own interpretation of each value - this became our values poster, which is displayed across the school and used on communications.\n\nA group of teachers have created a series of inputs for Registration over the last three years that highlight school updates, values and themes. Additionally, in 2025, we started looking at values-based assemblies, tying values to actions carried out in the school and communicating this directly to all young people..\n\nDigital badges have been awarded to young people that demonstrate values. These allow tracking of values-based actions by pupils, and this will appear on their awards certificate to indicate this.",
